oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Elvis and Governor's staff
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Elvis Presley visiting the Tennessee State Capitol, posing with Governor Buford Ellington and staff. Governor Buford Ellington's daughter, Ann (later Ann Ellington Wagner), stands beside of Elvis.

Elvis Presley (1935-1977) was an American singer and actor, dubbed the "King of Rock and Roll." He is regarded as one of the most significant cultural icons, as well as one of the most celebrated and influential musicians of the 20th century.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
